Nigerian midfielder, Ishaq Abdulrazak is set to link up with Belgian giants, Anderlecht from Swedish outfit, IFK Norrkopiing. Anderlecht, according to Sport Expressen, will pay IFK Norrkopiing â‚¬4.5m for the talented midfielder. The Belgian Pro League side have been scouting Abdulrazak for a while and had a bid for the player turned down by Norrkopiing early this year. The 20-year-old linked up with Norrkopiing from the local side Unity Academy in 2020. The Kaduna-born player has scored two goals in 37 league appearances for the Swedish club. This season, he has registered one assist in 10 league appearances.